Police are investigating after a teenage girl was bitten by a small black dog on Tuesday.
Officers said the incident happened on Tuesday at 17:10 outside the Co-Op at Charing Cross.
The girl, in a red jumper and black leggings, was crossing the zebra crossing outside the shop and was bitten on the leg, suffering a minor injury.
The dog, possibly a Manchester Terrier or Miniature Pinscher, had run up to her whilst she was on the road.
It is believed that the dog was with a man standing outside the shop at the time and he also had another similar dog with him.
Officers are appealing for anyone with information or who witnessed the incident to come forward.
